THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project fetches the following dependencies at build time via CMake
FetchContent. They are not redistributed in source form.

  google/benchmark v1.9.1 — Apache License 2.0
    https://github.com/google/benchmark

  catchorg/Catch2 v3.6.0 — Boost Software License 1.0
    https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2

  cwida/ALP — MIT License (optional, Clang-only build)
    https://github.com/cwida/ALP

The Gorilla XOR compression algorithm in include/lns/gorilla_codec.hpp
is a clean-room implementation of the algorithm described in:

  Pelkonen, T., Franklin, S., Teller, J., Cavallaro, P., Huang, Q.,
  Meza, J., and Veeraraghavan, K. (2015). Gorilla: A Fast, Scalable,
  In-Memory Time Series Database. Proc. VLDB Endow. 8(12), 1816–1827.
  https://doi.org/10.14778/2824032.2824078

No source code from the original Gorilla implementation was used.
The 6-bit leading-zero field extension is an intentional deviation
from the paper's 5-bit field; see RESULTS.md §Setup for rationale.
